BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:dst-forward-berlin-001
DTSTAMP:20260518T120000Z
SUMMARY:DST Forward Change Europe Berlin (dst-forward-berlin-001)
DESCRIPTION:Event spans DST spring forward where local clock skips from 02
 00 to 0300. Technically correct. Not Like in OSX-Ical, which removes an hour
 of this time zone defined end time.
DTSTART;TZID=Europe/Berlin:20260329T013000
DTEND;TZID=Europe/Berlin:20260329T043000
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:dst-forward-berlin-duration-2h
DTSTAMP:20260518T120000Z
SUMMARY:DST Forward Change Europe Berlin (dst-forward-berlin-duration-2h)
DESCRIPTION:Event spans DST spring forward where local clock skips from 02
 00 to 0300. This is WRONG result, as it should end on 2:30. Bit like in
 OSX iCal nobody cares. Plan your parties that ppl forget the time ;)
 --> Known issue.
DTSTART;TZID=Europe/Berlin:20260329T013000
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:dst-forward-berlin-duration-4h
DTSTAMP:20260518T120000Z
SUMMARY:DST Forward Change Europe Berlin (dst-forward-berlin-duration-4h)
DESCRIPTION:Event spans DST spring forward where local clock skips from 02
 00 to 0300. Actually the same WRONG result as OSX iCal implemets. It adds
 an hour practically, which we kindly ignore.
 --> Known issue.
DTSTART;TZID=Europe/Berlin:20260329T013000
DURATION:PT4H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:dst-backward-berlin-001
DTSTAMP:20260518T120000Z
SUMMARY:DST Backward Change Europe Berlin (dst-backward-berlin-001)
DESCRIPTION:Event spans DST fall back where hour repeats
DTSTART;TZID=Europe/Berlin:20261025T013000
DTEND;TZID=Europe/Berlin:20261025T043000
END:VEVENT
